Step 1: Download the google-cloud-cli

	https://dl.google.com/dl/cloudsdk/channels/rapid/downloads/google-cloud-cli-430.0.0-linux-x86_64.tar.gz

Step 2: Extract the contents of the file to any location on your file system

	tar -xf google-cloud-cli-430.0.0-linux-x86_64.tar.gz

Step 3:Add the gcloud CLI to your path

	./google-cloud-sdk/install.sh

Step 4:To view the available flags, run: 

	./google-cloud-sdk/install.sh --help

Step 5:To initialize the gcloud CLI, run gcloud init:

	./google-cloud-sdk/bin/gcloud init

Step 6: Sign in using your gmail address and password

Step 7: Check the gcloud versiuon
	gcloud --version
Step 8: Update gcloud components
	gcloud components update

Step 8: Install app engine for python

	gcloud components install app-engine-python
	
Step 10: Check the gcloud information
	gcloud info

